== Preparation ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into roughly 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into 1cm pieces. Cut the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g} into ½cm thick slices. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lemon{1/2}. Pick the @lemon thyme{4} leaves from their stalks (discard the stalks).

Lay out a sheet of #clingfilm{} and place a @British turkey steak{1} on top. Cover with another sheet of clingfilm. Using a #frying pan{} or a #rolling pin{}, bash the turkey until roughly 1cm thick. Repeat for @British turkey steak{1}. This can be very cathartic! Take the opportunity to work off any frustrations the day has thrown your way... Leave the turkey to one side.

> There are many ways you can tenderise meat. Marinating is good. Hanging works especially well for game. In some parts of the world they like to wrap stuff in papaya leaves. But our method of choice today is whacking the daylights out of some turkey with a frying pan! Simple, effective and fun...

== Pancetta Roasties ==

Put the potato chunks on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle over a glug of @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Sprinkle on the lemon thyme leaves and toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20%minutes}, then add the @pancetta lardons{60%g}. Cook until the potato and pancetta are both brown and crispy, ~{7-10%minutes}.

== Mushroom Sauce ==

Meanwhile, put a drizzle of @oil{} in your frying pan and place on a medium heat. Add the shallot and cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add another drizzle of oil and the mushrooms. Sprinkle over a generous pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Stir together and cook until the mushrooms are slightly browned, ~{6-7%minutes}. Squeeze in half the lemon juice and cook for a further ~{30%seconds}.

Turn the heat down to medium and stir in the @creme fraiche{100%g}. Taste and season with more salt, black pepper or lemon juice if needed, then set aside. Season each turkey steak with salt, black pepper and lemon zest. Heat a splash of @oil{} in another frying pan on medium heat. Once hot, add the turkey. Fry for ~{4-5%minutes} on each side, then remove to a #board{} to rest.

> TIP: The turkey is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When the potato and pancetta are browned and crispy, remove from the oven and add the @baby spinach{125%g} (there's a lot, but don't worry - it'll wilt down). Gently mix through the potato and return to the oven for ~{3%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat up the mushroom sauce (add a splash of @water{} if it's too thick) and cut the turkey steaks into 2cm wide slices. Serve the turkey with the pancetta roasties and a good spoonful of mushroom sauce. Enjoy!